OL,6,FToday she said that losing the benefit
OL,7,Fcould make her less likely to be able
OL,8,Fto stay in work. She said it felt as
OL,9,Fif government's always targeted
OL,10,Fdisabled people, most of whom wanted
OL,11,Fto work but for whom getting and
OL,12,Fkeeping a job can be difficult.
OL,14,FLouise Murphy, Senior Economist at the
OL,15,FResolution Foundation, said: "This
OL,16,Fpackage combines sensible reforms to
OL,17,Fincentivise and support people with
OL,18,Fpoor health back towards work, with
OL,19,Fhugely controversial cuts to non-work-
OL,20,Frelated disability benefits.
